Chess legend Bobby Fischer, facing prison in the US, can avoid deportation from Japan only if Iceland grants him full citizenship.
Japanese officials plan to deport him unless Iceland intervenes.
Despite Iceland offering residency, Fischer's US nationality complicates his case.
Recently, Iceland granted him citizenship, potentially preventing his extradition.
Fischer, known for his unpredictability, awaits resolution in Japan.
If granted Icelandic citizenship, he could travel freely.
Icelandic politicians are likely to approve his citizenship, allowing Fischer to make Iceland his new home.
Supporters anticipate his imminent release and return to Reykjavik, marking the end of his tumultuous journey.
